      "message": "[info] Line 448: The shared `emitted` set correctly prevents duplicate git_packbuilder_insert_commit calls, but the revwalk itself is not pruned: when the extra refs share most of their history with the conversation branch (the expected common case), each subsequent walk re-traverses the entire overlapping history, making this O(refs × history). Consider seeding later walks with git_revwalk_hide() for the already-emitted tips (or the have refs) to cut the redundant traversal.",
