      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 459: Inconsistent error handling inside the per-want loop: a failure of git_revwalk_new() does `return`, which abandons the entire pack (including refs already walked into the packbuilder) and, critically, skips the `onFetchedCb_(fetched)` call at the end. The sync counter in jamiaccount.cpp (syncCnt_) is then never decremented and ConversationCloned may never be emitted, stalling the clone. The two other per-want failures (git_oid_fromstr, git_revwalk_push) correctly `continue`. Prefer `continue` here as well so one bad ref doesn\u0027t abort the whole fetch:\n```suggestion\n        if (git_revwalk_new(\u0026walker_ptr, repo.get()) \u003c 0) {\n            continue;\n        }\n```",
      "revId": "459b45812710cf2e50b789a4ede8bbf270e166a9",
